<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-23T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-23T22:00:00-05:00" n="105" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/1925: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-24T11:00:00+08:00">October 24, 1939—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 24—7:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>935. Chairman of Municipal Council informs me that he visited the
                                Chinese Mayor yesterday afternoon accompanied by the Senior Consul
                                and the Japanese Consul General and that conversations will be
                                reopened with a view to seeking a settlement of the outside roads
                                problem, the Mayor requesting the Chairman to submit several
                                alternative proposals for consideration.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Chungking and Peiping, code text by air mail to
                                Tokyo.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>